                    "created": "2009-11-19T08:56:26.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-19T08:56:26.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/36171",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The following scenarios work:\r\n* Declarative usage\r\n** If the store is already defined prior to parsing, and the widget references the jsId of the store, then the value will be set.\r\n** If the store is already defined prior to parsing, but the widget does not define the store and the store is manually added to the widget following parsing, the value will _not_ be set.\r\n** If the store is already defined prior to parsing, but has no jsId, there's no way whatsoever to associate it with the widget; the value will _not_ be set.\r\n* Programmatic usage\r\n** The store _must_ be set and added as part of the widget declaration for the value to be set (i.e., added as an object, not as a string referencing the jsId)\r\n** Any other situation will result in no value being set\r\n\r\nThus, the only way for this to work is for the store declaration to happen prior to onLoad, and for the store declaration to define a jsId.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
